  "prompt": "What are the top 4 Common features for E-commerce software?",
  "response": "E-commerce software typically comes with a variety of features designed to help businesses manage and grow their online stores. Four common features that are considered essential for most e-commerce platforms include:\n\n1. **Product Management**:\n   - The ability to add, edit, and organize products is fundamental for any e-commerce software. This includes handling product descriptions, pricing, categories, images, and inventory tracking.\n\n2. **Shopping Cart & Checkout**:\n   - A robust shopping cart and checkout system is critical for a smooth customer experience. Features often include support for multiple payment gateways, a secure payment process, and cart recovery options.\n\n3. **Order Management**:\n   - Efficiently managing orders, from processing to fulfillment, is crucial. Features may include order tracking, customer notifications, and integrations with shipping carriers for handling deliveries.\n\n4. **SEO & Marketing Tools**:\n   - Built-in SEO features and marketing tools help attract and retain customers. Common tools include options for setting meta tags, creating promo codes, email marketing integrations, and analytics to measure traffic and sales performance.\n\nThese features collectively help ensure that e-commerce businesses can operate smoothly, provide a good customer experience, and effectively promote their products.",
